To gain an understanding of the raw data I looked at a snapshot of each data set (e.g., 20 rows SELECT TOP 20 * FROM bronze.gender_submission;).
This helped me to understand how the data had been split across datasets, where it can be joined. 

I then did some basic checks on each of the datasets to see whether there were any nulls, duplicates or outliers within the data that may cause difficulty later.
This allowed me to understand that train.csv contained PassengerIDs and their related columns for 1-891 whereas gender_submission.csv
only contained the Survived Status for passengers 892-1309 with test.csv containing the rows it lacked and when combined it covers 
all the data for passengers 892-1309.

Tests on each of these datasets allowed me to identify areas of missing information, what requires standardisation and gave me
sufficient information to transform this data at the next layer.

