/* 

WITH test_table AS (

SELECT * FROM bronze.train

UNION ALL

SELECT 
	t.PassengerID,
	gs.Survived,
	t.Pclass,
	t.Name,
	t.Sex,
	t.Age,
	t.SibSp,
	t.Parch,
	t.Ticket,
	t.Fare,
	t.Cabin,
	t.Embarked
FROM bronze.test t
JOIN bronze.gender_submission gs
	ON t.PassengerID = gs.PassengerID
)
SELECT * FROM test_table;
*/

The test table gives us all 3 of the bronze tables into one overall table 
allowing for easier testing of columns as well as ensuring all passenger data has correctly been added.
Once established it is correct and combined data has been formatted, this can then be split into fact and dimension tables for the gold layer.
